This outwins the gain of 18% seen in the Nasdaq 100  which is a primary growth stock index.It isnâ€™t surprising as that period was a recovery phase from Covid-19 when demands started to increase and households had cash on hand from the generous stimulus program.Fate changed from late March onwards as Nasdaq climbed 27% compared to a mere 8% gain in the value fund.ğŸŸThe Outlook for Value & GrowthğŸ”¦The question requires us to assume economic growth for 2022. Pika World expects a material slow down in 2022 compared to 2021. This  therefore  works poorly for value stocks. Nonetheless  many value stocks are already pricing in for the slower growth.
